{"lemma":"غَضَّ","slug":"غَضَّ","root":"غ.ض.ض","root_slug":"غ-ض-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ض-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31937"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lower (one's gaze or voice)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put down, to belittle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be fresh, to be tender (of a plant)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be radiant (of a woman's skin, etc.)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fresh, tender, radiant (of plants and women)","examples":[{"text":"وأما اختزان القنبيط والرازيانج الغض لمن أحب أن يأكلها في غير أيامها فيخزن ذلك في الخل على ما أصف يؤخذ قلوب القنبيط وينصف ويغمر في الخل ويجعل فيه شيء من الفوذنج ويطين رأس الإناء ويرفع وأما فضبان الرازيانج الغض فينشر ويعمل بها مثل ذلك.","english":"In what concerns the preservation of cauliflower and fresh fennel, for him who likes to eat them off-season, these get preserved in vinegar in the following fashion: One takes the hearts of the cauliflower and halves and dunks into the vinegar and puts some pennyroyal into it and daubs the head of the receptacle and lifts it, and for the stalks of the fresh fennel, they are spread and the same is done with them."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَضَّ (ḡaḍḍa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"],"examples":[{"text":"غَضّ البَصَر","english":"lowering of one's gaze"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the spadix of a palm-tree"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31937","headword_ar":"غَضٌّ","root":"gD","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh; juicy; sappy: moist; not flaccid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) applied to a thing, (S, Msb,) whatever it be; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDiyDF","text_ar":"غَضِيضً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. K,) Hence the trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano sar~ahu A^ano yaqoraA^u AlquroA=na gaD~FA kamaA","text_ar":"مَنْ سَرَّهُ اَنْ يَقْرَاُ القُرْا=نَ غَضًّا كَمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazala faloyaqoraA^o qiraA='apa A@boni A^am~i EabodK","text_ar":"نَزَلَ فَلْيَقْرَاْ قِرَا=ءَةَ ا@بْنِ اَمِّ عَبْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who is rejoiced"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleased, to read the Kur-an freshly, who as it descended, let him read according to the reading of Ibn-Umm-'Abd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  A calf"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recently born:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giDaADN","text_ar":"غِضَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  Anything (S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful and bright;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;,) as (assumed tropical:)  youth, and the like: (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaD~N","text_ar":"غَضٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to youth, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaD~apN","text_ar":"غَضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a woman, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baD~N","text_ar":"بَضٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baD~apN","text_ar":"بَضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thinskinned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine-skinned, and plump:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. j: (A:) or the latter, applied to a woman, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin-shinned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine-skinned, so that the blood appears"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Lh:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDiyDapN","text_ar":"غَضِيضَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is thus applied like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaD~apN","text_ar":"غَضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N baD~N gaD~N","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ بَضٌّ غَضٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAD~N gaAD~N","text_ar":"بَاضٌّ غَاضٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and beautiful and bright;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a flourishing condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the worse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabotu gaD~N","text_ar":"نَبْتُ غَضٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh and flourishing and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender plant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N gaD~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ غَضٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shade which the sun has not reached;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like a plant which the sun has not reached. (TA.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spadix of a palm-tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloEN","text_ar":"طَلْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDiyDN","text_ar":"غَضِيضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar:) or both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tender"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tender"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it appears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it appears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S:) or the same,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit when it first comes forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","A","Lh","IAar","K","TA","As"]}]}}